DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:The act of gathering things together; having been brought together in one place.:A shortened version of a speech or written text, containing only the main points._Quantity; how much there is of something that you can measure._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
